Description


 The Big Data Analyst assists in proving actionable insights through analyses of large structured and unstructured datasets from unrelated sources. They ensure the delivery of future predictions based on previous data patterns to provide solutions to business problems and requirements.The Big Data Analyst assists business decisions using data science and statistical analysis through the wide ranges of data available to them, ensuring scalability in order to deliver the Big Data strategy and achieve business objectives.Typically reports to the Big Data Analytics Manager.






 Demonstrates deep understanding of modelling techniques, algorithms and being able to tune, modify and implement changes to address different business questions;
 Provides deep technical analytical and data expertise to the business and other Data Scientists, using a wide variety of available data, to solve complex business problems;
 Develops key predictive models and products;
 Develops and deploys statistical models to include machine learning models;
 Delivers coding solutions for complex Use Cases based on commercial requirements;
 Constantly monitors and optimizes performance of developed models by driving experiments, benchmarking, etc.;
 Uses a variety of datasets to test hypotheses, discover hidden relationships and provide actionable insights to Vodafone�s businesses;
 Uses data visualisation to engage audience in a compelling way, enabling effective storytelling;
 Delivers key packages of work, on time and in a collaborative manner to meet the needs of business customers;
 Uses communication skills to exchange ideas and information in a concise and logical way to work in partnership with Technology and local BI and analytics teams in order to agree on pragmatic means of data provision to support use cases;
 Effectively interacts with stakeholders across the business to advise and help solve complex problems;
 Performs other job-related duties or tasks defined by the manager or resulting from assigned agendas.





 Skills



  Data Modelling


  Data Visualisation


  Data Analytics and Insights


  Data Management and Transformation


  AI - Deep and Machine Learning and AR


  Leading Organisation Culture and Change


  Strategic Mindset



Description


 The Data Engineer will support their functional area across Vodafone Business Platform Solutions (VBPS) and generate insights by supporting fact-based decision making using business data. This includes implementing and managing data elaboration flows with a view to provide KPIs, metrics, trends and visual (digital) storyboards using a variety of technologies and analytical techniques. Working with the operational teams to target areas of opportunity or improvement and maximise business value through combining web based analytics and data warehousing to enable profound insights. The role may require the importing, cleaning, transforming, validating or modelling of data with the purpose of understanding or making conclusions from the data for decision-making purposes. Typically reports to the Chapter Lead.
 #_VOIS




 Job Responsibility



 Drives development and implementation of squad�s analytics strategy and roadmap, incl. data source selection, data collection, transformation and standard reporting;
 May extract, load or transform data from different sources either via scripting (e.g. SQL) or coding (e.g. Python);
 May use predictive or descriptive analytics models;
 Visualises and translates business requirements into concrete data engineering tasks;
 Develops and deploys standard reports on squad KPIs and key operating metrics to enable continuous monitoring and improvement;
 Develops smart and insightful dashboards and reports, tracking performance across channels to promote data-driven decision-making and optimize conversion;
 Presents data in charts, graphs, tables, designing and developing relational databases for collecting data and building or designing data input or data collection screens;
 Leads continuous, data-based improvement of activities via A/B testing and behavioural analysis;
 Provides deep-dive analyses, generates insights and handles ad-hoc queries on a broad range of questions, (e.g. to define business strategies, specify product offerings, campaign performance, customer profiling, data quality investigations, testing);
 May further build the data technology and systems landscape through integrating new data sources to the DWH or advancing existing tracking technology.





